      "solution": "<p><strong>CORRECT ANSWER:</strong> <strong>C) 1-ii, 2-iv, 3-i, 4-iii</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>EXPLANATION:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Amyloidosis is a condition characterised by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ba366417791692777187229d34e597\">extracellular</span> deposits of fibrillar proteins. These <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"458e050fdc16927771809854c9fd53\">abnormal</span> fibrils are produced by the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a00e90be0416927771803afbbf099b\">aggregation</span> of misfolded proteins.</p>\n\n<p>Important amyloid-disease associations:</p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Disease</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Amyloid</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Multiple <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"aa6a0dfcb61692777193561ed10fac\">myeloma</span> and other <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b2b82438d6169277719287eb450079\">monoclonal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a0e40688fa169277719572bdb48c92\">plasma</span> cell disorders</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>AL</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Chronic inflammation</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>AA</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Alzheimer’s disease</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Aβ</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Familial <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51ad856e041692777181f80c9d507a\">amyloid</span> polyneuropathy</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>ATTR (mutated <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a1b06f401f1692777203a53393ba98\">form</span> of transthyretin)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Diabetes mellitus</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>AIAPP</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Hemodialysis associated amyloidosis</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Aβ<sub>2</sub>m</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Familial Meditterean Fever</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>AA</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Senile <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8f2e7fd96116927771995b451b5c90\">systemic</span> amyloidosis</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>ATTR (Increased quantity of TTR, no <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7a67bdf6f81692777193cfd480f228\">mutation</span> is seen)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Medullary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"988c19e3131692777183b6744d1920\">carcinoma</span> of the thyroid</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Acal</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Isolated atrial amyloidosis</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>AANF</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Types: </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Primary amyloidosis.</strong>\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Seen in <strong>multiple myeloma</strong> and other <strong>monoclonal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a0e40688fa169277719572bdb48c92\">plasma</span> cell proliferations</strong>.</li>\n\t\t<li><strong>AL type</strong> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"959f3344b116927771815235718f3d\">amyloidosis</span> is seen.</li>\n\t\t<li>Amyloid <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"578fe8d7dd16927771913c847ed254\">light chain</span> (AL) protein is made up of complete <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f8fab286571692777189bdfd087071\">immunoglobulin</span> light chains, the amino-terminal fragments of light chains, or both.</li>\n\t\t<li>Most of the AL proteins analyzed are composed of λ light chains or their fragments, but κ chains are present in some cases.</li>\n\t\t<li>The AL type of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51ad856e041692777181f80c9d507a\">amyloid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5303b168291692777202506efbdeb9\">fibril</span> protein is produced from <strong>free Ig light chains</strong> secreted by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b2b82438d6169277719287eb450079\">monoclonal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a0e40688fa169277719572bdb48c92\">plasma</span> cells.</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Secondary amyloidosis.</strong></p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>",
